# Extra Mounts - Claude Code Sandbox
#
# Mount additional host directories into the container alongside
# the project directory. Useful for files that live outside the
# project tree — downloads, datasets, logs, shared libraries, etc.
#
# Every entry here applies to all projects. For one-off mounts,
# use the --mount flag instead (see GUIDE.md).
#
# To use: copy this file to mounts.conf and uncomment/edit entries.
#   cp mounts.conf.example mounts.conf
#
# Format: /absolute/host/path|relative/path/in/project|mode
#
#   host-path     = absolute path on the host (~ is expanded)
#   relative-path = where it appears inside the project in the container
#   mode          = ro (read-only) or rw (read-write). Defaults to ro
#
# Changes take effect on next run. No rebuild needed.
# Lines starting with # are comments. Blank lines are ignored.
#
# ── Common Mounts ────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# ~/Shared|shared|ro
# ~/Downloads|tmp/downloads|ro
#
# ── Application Logs ────────────────────────────────────────
# Mount log files from a service running on the host so Claude
# can help analyze errors, performance issues, or patterns.
#
# /var/log/myapp|logs/host|ro
# ~/.pm2/logs|logs/pm2|ro
#
# ── Datasets ────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Large datasets stored on a separate drive or outside the
# project tree. Avoids duplicating gigabytes of data.
#
# /mnt/data/training-images|data/training|ro
# ~/datasets/clickstream-2026|data/raw|ro
#
# ── Shared Libraries / Components ───────────────────────────
# A folder of reusable code, UI components, or utilities
# shared across multiple projects.
#
# ~/dev/shared-ui-components|lib/shared-ui|ro
# ~/dev/design-tokens|src/tokens|ro
#
# ── Reference Docs / Specs ─────────────────────────────────
# API specs, architecture docs, or design documents stored
# in a central location outside any single project.
#
# ~/Documents/api-specs|docs/specs|ro
# ~/Documents/design-system|docs/design|ro
#
# ── Internal / Synced Docs ─────────────────────────────────
# Gitignored internal docs synced across machines (e.g., via
# Syncthing, Dropbox, or similar). Keeps private notes
# available without committing them to version control.
#
# ~/internal-docs|docs/internal|ro
#
# ── Writable Output (read-write) ───────────────────────────
# A writable directory for generated output, exports, or
# scratch files that should persist outside the project.
# Use rw instead of ro when the agent needs to write here.
# Omitting the mode defaults to ro.
#
# ~/shared-output|output|rw
# ~/exports|data/exports|rw
